---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is NO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)" description="NO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a refusal or denial. Extensions include NOB, NOD, NOR, NOS, NOT, NOW. Strategy guide inside." keywords="is no a scrabble word, no scrabble, no valid scrabble, no points scrabble, two letter n words, no meaning scrabble, no extensions scrabble">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is NO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)","description":"NO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It means a refusal or denial.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-no-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is NO a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, NO is valid in both TWL (North American) and SOWPODS (International) Scrabble dictionaries. It scores 2 points (N=1, O=1) and means a negative reply, refusal, or denial. It's also used as a noun (plural: noes or nos)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you extend NO into?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"NO extends into many common words: NOB (5pts), NOD (4pts), NOR (3pts), NOS (3pts), NOT (3pts), NOW (6pts), NOG (4pts). NOW is the strongest at 6 points thanks to W(4)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Should I play NO or save my N for a longer word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"N is worth only 1 point and is common (6 tiles in bag). Playing NO is fine when it creates crosswords or sets up extensions like NOW or NOB. But avoid wasting N on a standalone 2-point play when better options exist — N is useful in common endings like -ING and -TION."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/two-letter-words/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</a>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is NO a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>4 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Yes, NO is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS. It's one of the most basic English words — a refusal, denial, or negative reply. While only 2 points on its own, NO extends into many common 3-letter words like NOW (6pts) and NOB (5pts), making it a solid setup play.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">NO</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 points · N=1, O=1 · A refusal or negative reply</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS (Collins Scrabble Words). NO is one of the first words any English speaker learns. As a noun it can be pluralized (noes/nos). Its value in Scrabble comes from its many extensions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">TWL + SOWPODS</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6 N-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the Bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 O-tiles</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">NO Extensions: Many Common Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOW</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-amber-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOB</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOG</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOS</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">NOT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">NO Strategy: When to Play It</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Setup for NOW:</span> Play NO near a W-friendly spot. NOW (6pts) is a common extension that scores well. The NO→NOW→KNOWN chain shows how 2-letter setups cascade into higher-value plays.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Cross-word filler:</span> NO is perfect for parallel plays. N and O both form valid crosswords with many letters. Play NO next to existing words to pick up bonus cross-points without using valuable tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Preserve N for -ING:</span> N is crucial for the -ING ending in bingos. Don't waste N on a standalone NO play unless you're creating crosswords or setting up extensions. N in your rack keeps bingo potential alive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Front Hooks on NO</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">NO can be front-hooked to make longer words: <span class="text-white font-medium">KNOW (11pts), SNOW (7pts)</span>. If your opponent plays NO, you can capitalize by adding letters in front. Be aware of this when you play NO — you might be setting up your opponent too.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-na-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is NA a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-en-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is EN a Scrabble Word? Yes! (Score 2 Points)</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
